  "faq": {
    "header": "# --- Frequently Asked Questions ---",
    "title": "FAQ",
    "general": "General",
    "participation": "Participation",
    "venueLogistics": "Venue and Logistics",
    "projectDevelopment": "Project Development",
    "q1": "What is HackNU?",
    "a1": "HackNU is a 24-hour hackathon organized by ACM Student Chapter at Nazarbayev University. It is one of the biggest student hackathons in Central Asia.",
    "q2": "When and where will HackNU/26 take place?",
    "a2": "HackNU/26 will take place on October 18-19, 2026 at Nazarbayev University in Astana, Kazakhstan.",
    "q3": "Is HackNU free to attend?",
    "a3": "Yes! HackNU is completely free for all participants. We provide meals, snacks, swag, and prizes.",
    "q4": "Who can participate?",
    "a4": "Any student currently enrolled at a university or college can participate. We welcome participants of all skill levels.",
    "q5": "Can I participate alone?",
    "a5": "Teams should consist of 2-4 members. If you don't have a team, you can find teammates during our team-forming session at the beginning of the event.",
    "q6": "Do I need programming experience?",
    "a6": "While some programming knowledge is helpful, we welcome participants of all skill levels. HackNU is a great place to learn and grow!",
    "q7": "Will food be provided?",
    "a7": "Yes! We will provide meals, snacks, and beverages throughout the 24-hour event.",
    "q8": "Can I sleep at the venue?",
    "a8": "The venue will be open 24 hours. We recommend bringing a sleeping bag or blanket if you plan to rest during the event.",
    "q9": "What should I bring?",
    "a9": "Bring your laptop, charger, any hardware you want to hack with, and your student ID. We'll provide everything else!",
    "q10": "Are there specific tracks or themes?",
    "a10": "Yes, we will announce the competition tracks and themes closer to the event. Stay tuned on our social media channels.",
    "q11": "Can I start working on my project before the event?",
    "a11": "No, all work must be done during the 24-hour hackathon period. You can brainstorm ideas beforehand, but no code should be written in advance.",
    "q12": "What tools and technologies can I use?",
    "a12": "You can use any programming language, framework, or tool you want. There are no restrictions on technology choices."
  },
